---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Intelligence, amplified" description="Practical guidance for applying Copilot, agents, and AI tools to real work.">
  <article style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;">
    <header class="about-hero" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Commit Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--text-meta); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        About
      </p>
      <h1 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.2; color: var(--text-primary);">
        Intelligence, <em style="color: var(--accent);">amplified</em>
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.75;">
      <p>
        Intelligence, amplified is a practical resource for people trying to make AI useful in everyday professional work.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        The focus is not broad predictions or product hype. It is practical adoption: where Copilot helps,
        where agents fit, how prompts change the quality of the work, and what new platform updates actually
        mean for people using these tools inside real organizations.
      </p>

      <p>
        IA stands for intelligence amplification. The point is not to replace human judgment. The point is to
        extend it: reduce routine effort, surface useful context, and create more room for analysis, creativity,
        decision-making, and follow-through.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        What you’ll find here
      </h2>
      <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
        <li style="padding: 0.85rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);"><strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">Guides</strong><br />Step-by-step walkthroughs for Microsoft 365 Copilot, agents, and related tools. These are built for people who want to try the workflow, not just read about it.</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.85rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);"><strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">Use cases</strong><br />Scenario-based examples that connect AI capabilities to real business work across roles, teams, and industries.</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.85rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);"><strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">News and updates</strong><br />A scannable roll-up of official Microsoft announcements, organized so you can see what changed, why it matters, and where to read the source.</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.85rem 0;"><strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">Practical observations</strong><br />Short notes from hands-on AI-assisted work: what worked, what was awkward, what improved the workflow, and what still needs judgment.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        What this is not
      </h2>
      <p>
        This is not an official Microsoft resource, a product blog, or a replacement for documentation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
